This flat merged list is a deliberate UI decision — the spec comment at the top of the file says "Unified vocabulary settings — one flat word list + mining suggestions inline" — so users see one list, not two separate sections. The dual-ViewModel backing also explains why `requestRemove` must check `replacementsVM` when computing `pendingDeleteLinkedRules` for the cascade-delete dialog: removing a word from `wordsVM` alone leaves orphaned rules in `replacementsVM` unless explicitly cleaned up.

