This pattern serves two purposes. First, `UserDefaults.set(_:forKey:)` is not free — it serializes data and can trigger KVO notifications and plist I/O. Calling it on every observation cycle (e.g., during SwiftUI's `@Observable` diffing pass) would create unnecessary disk writes. Second, `storage.logSettingChange` presumably writes a structured log entry; emitting duplicate log lines whenever the UI re-renders would produce misleading audit trails.

