In `Services/Audio/AudioCaptureService.swift`, the `AudioCaptureService` protocol defines `warmUp()`, `coolDown()`, and `setTimingSessionID(_:)` as optional-by-convention hooks by providing empty default bodies in the `extension AudioCaptureService` block at the bottom of the file.

This pattern exists because not every concrete conformer needs these capabilities. `warmUp()` is documented as a way to prime the audio stack so that subsequent `startCapture()` calls are faster without keeping an idle engine or microphone path alive — it is an optimization hint, not a correctness requirement. Similarly, `coolDown()` clears warm-up bookkeeping without touching active recording teardown, which is handled separately. `setTimingSessionID(_:)` pipes a `TimingSession` id into the capture path so the HAL tap thread can stamp timing phases (`p05_first_sample`, `p12*`) without a back-channel — useful only when timing instrumentation is active.

By placing no-op defaults in the extension:
```swift
